---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="INFO" description="About Nick Chimicles" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="about-intro">
				<div class="container">
					<h1>HISTORY<br />& AI</h1>
					<div class="about-grid">
						<div class="about-content">
							<p>
								My research combines rigorous historical scholarship with computational methods to uncover new insights about the past and their implications for the present.
							</p>

							<p>
								Currently building a new AI-powered archive at Arkeon. My previous work includes HistoryLab AI, which makes declassified documents searchable, and Gnosis, which transforms complex texts into interactive learning experiences.
							</p>

							<p>
								I believe technology should serve human understanding, not replace it. My thesis on WWII strategic bombing was recognized with Columbia's Alan J. Willen Memorial Prize for challenging 80 years of historical narrative using data-driven methods.
							</p>

							<p>
								I write on <a href="https://substack.com/@nacwrites" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Substack</a> about technology, culture, and ideas. My main publication, <a href="https://politicalatheism.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Political Atheism</a>, applies René Girard's mimetic theory to literature, culture, and contemporary society through close readings, philosophical analysis, and computational modeling.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="about-details">
							<div class="detail-section">
								<h3 class="mono">CONTACT</h3>
								<p><a href="mailto:nick@arkeon.tech">nick@arkeon.tech</a></p>
								<p><a href="https://x.com/real_nac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@real_nac</a></p>
								<p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-a-chimicles-1a0234175/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a></p>
								<p><a href="https://github.com/nac-codes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></p>
							</div>
							<div class="detail-section">
								<h3 class="mono">EXPERTISE</h3>
								<p>Historical Research</p>
								<p>AI Application & Integration</p>
								<p>Full-Stack Engineering</p>
								<p>Digital Humanities</p>
							</div>
							<div class="detail-section">
								<h3 class="mono">EDUCATION</h3>
								<p>Columbia University, 2025</p>
								<p>History & Computer Science</p>
								<p>Alan J. Willen Prize</p>
							</div>
							<div class="detail-section">
								<h3 class="mono">CURRENT</h3>
								<p>Building @ Arkeon</p>								
								<p>New York, NY</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
			
			<section class="publications">
				<div class="container">
					<h2 class="mono">PUBLICATIONS</h2>
					<div class="publications-grid">
						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">Political Atheism</span>
								<span class="publication-date">November 19, 2025</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://politicalatheism.substack.com/p/the-math-of-the-mob" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Math of the Mob</a></h3>
							<p>Why scapegoating is computationally efficient, morally arbitrary, and foundational to human culture</p>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">Political Atheism</span>
								<span class="publication-date">October 26, 2025</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://politicalatheism.substack.com/p/why-your-politics-decides-what-you-drink" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Why Your Politics Decides What You Drink</a></h3>
							<p>How mimetic desire goes from Brussels sprouts and Bud Light boycotts to dead group chats and ideological crusade</p>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">The Sundial</span>
								<span class="publication-date">April 23, 2025</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://www.sundial-cu.org/p/he-outsmarted-amazon-columbia-kicked" target="_blank" rel="noopener">He Outsmarted Amazon. Columbia Kicked Him Out.</a></h3>
							<p>Roy Lee was suspended for developing an AI tool to ace coding interviews—now his company is raking in over $200k a month</p>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">The Sundial</span>
								<span class="publication-date">October 31, 2024</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://www.sundial-cu.org/p/the-decline-of-conservative-thought" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Decline of Conservative Thought in Academia</a></h3>
							<p>A conversation with Professor Mark Lilla</p>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">The Sundial</span>
								<span class="publication-date">September 1, 2024</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://www.sundial-cu.org/p/where-did-the-intellectual-clash" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Where Did The Intellectual Clash Go?</a></h3>
							<p>Contemporary Civilization's syllabus has lost the diversity of intellectual opinion that once characterized the Core's first class</p>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">The Sundial</span>
								<span class="publication-date">March 27, 2024</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://www.sundial-cu.org/p/meet-us-at-the-sundial" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meet Us at the Sundial</a></h3>
							<p>Reviving an old publication to spread new ideas</p>
							<small class="co-authors">With Jonas Du and Jackson Cheramie</small>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">The Sundial</span>
								<span class="publication-date">March 24, 2024</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://www.sundial-cu.org/p/the-ballad-of-mels-burger-bar" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Ballad of Mel's Burger Bar</a></h3>
							<p>An elegy for an egalitarian eden</p>
						</article>

						<article class="publication-item">
							<div class="publication-meta">
								<span class="publication-venue">Columbia Independent</span>
								<span class="publication-date">March 1, 2023</span>
							</div>
							<h3><a href="https://rh4llcdim3lmdksfy5wjcnj6bi2qq5zbnakq5ix2zybnir3nkoda.arweave.net/ifi1iGhm1sGqRcdskTU-CjUIdyFoFQ6i-s4C1EdtU4Y" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Say Goodbye to Your Future</a></h3>
							<p>Why the jobs we want are going away, and what to do instead</p>
						</article>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about-intro {
		padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
	}

	.about-intro h1 {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
		line-height: 0.9;
	}

	.about-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
		gap: var(--space-2xl);
		align-items: start;
	}

	.about-content p {
		color: var(--gray-300);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.about-details {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-xl);
	}

	.detail-section h3 {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: var(--gray-400);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
	}

	.detail-section p {
		color: var(--gray-200);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xs) 0;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		line-height: 1.4;
	}

	.detail-section a {
		color: var(--gray-200);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.detail-section a:hover {
		color: var(--white);
	}

	/* Publications Section */
	.publications {
		padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-800);
	}

	.publications h2 {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: var(--gray-400);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
	}

	.publications-grid {
		display: grid;
		gap: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.publication-item {
		padding: var(--space-md) 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-900);
	}

	.publication-item:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.publication-meta {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		color: var(--gray-500);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
	}

	.publication-venue {
		color: var(--gray-400);
	}

	.publication-item h3 {
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm) 0;
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		line-height: 1.4;
	}

	.publication-item h3 a {
		color: var(--white);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.publication-item h3 a:hover {
		color: var(--gray-300);
	}

	.publication-item p {
		color: var(--gray-400);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-xs) 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.co-authors {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		color: var(--gray-500);
		font-style: italic;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.about-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: var(--space-xl);
		}

		.about-details {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
			gap: var(--space-lg);
		}

		.publication-meta {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
			gap: var(--space-xs);
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		.about-details {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: var(--space-lg);
		}
	}
</style>
